#import "/_lib/0.1.1.typ": *
#show: template

#taxon[Definition]
#title[open embedding]

An open embedding is a morphism $pi: (X, Oo_X) ->  (Y, Oo_Y)$ that factors as
$
  (X, Oo_X) ->^~  (U, Oo_Y|U) ->  (Y, Oo_Y),
$
where the first map is an isomorphism and the second is the inclusion of the open set $U subset Y$ into $Y$ (as a ringed space). In this situation, we often write $X arrow.hook Y$.
